I'm glad you did some looking and I'm not surprised at what you saw.
NT's speed and size optimizations are not "free".

MS has always optimzed, in very compromising ways, their Windows
OS's.  That is what makes windows3.1 faster and it's also a consequent of
MS's evolving technology where the continually graft on to their codebase:
